[ edit ] Current MEPs Further information: MEPs for Germany 2004-2009
[ edit ] 1979 Further information: European Parliament election, 1979 (West Germany)
In European elections , Germany is a constituency of the European Parliament , currently represented by ninety-nine members . It covers the member state of Germany .
The 1979 European election was the first direct election to the European Parliament to be held and hence the first time Germany had voted.
This article is about the European Parliament constituency. For the country, see Germany . For all other uses, see Germany (disambiguation) .
Please help improve this section by expanding it.
Further information might be found on the talk page or at requests for expansion .
